<h1>Community Guidelines</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 11/3/2025<br />
     <strong>Last Updated:</strong> 11/3/2025</p>

  <p>These Community Guidelines outline the standards of behavior expected from all players and participants in the <strong>RPGame.Live</strong> community, including Discord servers, in-game chat, and related platforms.</p>

  <p>By engaging with the community, you agree to follow these guidelines. Violations may result in warnings, suspensions, bans, or other enforcement actions.</p>

  <h2>1. Respect and Inclusion</h2>
  <p>We welcome players of all backgrounds. You agree to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Treat others with respect and courtesy</li>
    <li>Avoid harassment, hate speech, or discrimination</li>
    <li>Use inclusive language and avoid personal attacks</li>
    <li>Respect pronouns, identities, and boundaries</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Fair Play and Integrity</h2>
  <p>We value honest competition and fair gameplay. You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Exploit bugs, glitches, or unintended mechanics</li>
    <li>Use unauthorized bots, scripts, or automation</li>
    <li>Share or promote cheats, hacks, or exploits</li>
    <li>Impersonate staff or other players</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Content and Communication</h2>
  <p>You are responsible for what you share. You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Post or link to offensive, illegal, or explicit content</li>
    <li>Spam messages, emojis, or promotional material</li>
    <li>Share private information without consent</li>
    <li>Disrupt conversations or derail threads</li>
  </ul>
  <p><em>Note:</em> Moderators may remove content or mute users at their discretion.</p>

  <h2>4. Usernames and Avatars</h2>
  <p>Your display name and avatar must:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Avoid offensive, misleading, or impersonating content</li>
    <li>Follow platform-specific rules (e.g., Discord’s username policies)</li>
    <li>Be appropriate for all audiences</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Moderator Authority</h2>
  <p>Moderators and admins are here to help. You agree to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Follow instructions from staff and moderators</li>
    <li>Avoid arguing about moderation decisions in public channels</li>
    <li>Use designated appeal or feedback channels if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Reporting and Enforcement</h2>
  <p>If you witness a violation:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the appropriate report tools or contact a moderator</li>
    <li>Do not engage in retaliation or escalation</li>
    <li>Trust that reports will be reviewed fairly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Updates and Changes</h2>
  <p>These guidelines may be updated as the community grows. Changes will be posted with a revised “Last Updated” date.</p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>For questions or concerns about these guidelines, contact:<br />
     📧 <strong>Support@RPGame.Live</strong><br /></p>

  <footer>
    <p>These Community Guidelines are part of the legal and social framework governing your participation in <strong>RPGame.Live</strong>.</p>
  </footer>


